cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.SY

This paper proposes a technique to improve the training of adversarial models, which is a common topic in machine learning and artificial intelligence research (cs.LG, cs.AI). The proposed method is applied to three distinct application areas: imitation learning of dynamic continuous control skills (cs.RO), adversarial inverse reinforcement learning (cs.AI), and GANs for image generation (cs.CV). Therefore, the paper could also be categorized under cs.RO and cs.CV. Additionally, the paper involves the use of constraints to modulate the discriminator's accuracy, which is a topic related to control systems (cs.SY).
